'''Michael Kogge''' is an [[Wikipedia:Americans|American]] [[Wikipedia:Screenwriter|screenwriter]] and [[Wikipedia:Author|author]] who has written for several ''[[Star Wars]]'' projects, including the ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]'', ''[[Star Wars Gamer]]'' magazine, [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]], ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine, and the ''[[Star Wars: Edge of the Empire]]'' [[roleplaying game]]. He has also authored a series of [[Star Wars Rebels chapter books|''Star Wars Rebels'' chapter books]], adapting episodes from the series' [[Star Wars Rebels Season One|first season]]. He served as Head Writer for the groundbreaking AR (augmented reality) video game ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Challenges]]''.

==Biography==
Michael Kogge writes for the ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' in addition to having penned material for [[The Topps Company, Inc.|Topps]], [[West End Games]], [[Fantasy Flight Games]], the ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]'', [[Wizards of the Coast]], and ''[[Star Wars Gamer]]''.

He scripted the four-part web series [[Xim Week: The Despotica|'' The Despotica'']] for [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace's]] "[[Xim/Legends|Xim]] Week" in [[2009]]. The fifth part of the series, "[[The Gleam of Kiirium]]," a poem he wrote for ''[[The Essential Guide to Warfare]]'', was published in [[2013]] on The Official ''Star Wars'' Blog.

In "[[The Business of Bacta]]," he created the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Thyferra/Legends|Thyferra]] and the background for [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]].

His original comic series published by Alterna Comics, the Roman epic ''Empire of the Wolf'', incorporates many of the same classic mythic themes as ''Star Wars''.<ref name="Empire">{{Comixology|url=Empire-of-the-Wolf-1/digital-comic/53829|text=''Empire of the Wolf''}}</ref> He has also written for Blizzard's StarCraft universe and stories set on Edgar Rice Burroughs's Barsoom/Mars.

His website is [http://www.michaelkogge.com michaelkogge.com]; the ''Star Wars'' link on the site links to this biography.

